properties.name: Advice
properties.webBody:
The Threat is Reduced following the grassfire at Charlton-Jeffcott Rd, Wooroonook. 
  • This Advice message replaces the Advice message issued on Thursday 18 December 2025 at 10:30PM.
People located within Charlton, Woosang, Yeungroon, Yeungroon East are now able to resume normal activities but should remain vigilant.
Impacts in your area: 
  • The following road remains closed: Charlton-St Arnaud Road.
  • Check the VicTraffic Website or call 13 11 70 for road closures. 
  • Emergency services will remain in the area and continue to monitor.
  • Smoke may be visible from nearby communities and roads.
This message was issued by Country Fire Authority.   

Use multiple sources to stay informed: 
  • www.emergency.vic.gov.au 
  • VicEmergency Hotline - freecall 1800 226 226 
  • VicEmergency app 
  • Facebook or Twitter (#vicfires) 
  • Tune in to ABC Local Radio, commercial and designated community radio stations, or Sky News TV. 
Accessibility: 
The following services can help you, or someone you know, access information during an emergency. 
  • To access this information in other languages, call the Translating and Interpreting Service on 131 450 (freecall) and ask them to call VicEmergency Hotline.   
  • If you are deaf, hard of hearing, or have a speech/communication impairment contact National Relay Service for assistance and ask them to call the VicEmergency Hotline.

properties.name: Advice
properties.location: Goomalibee, between Frazers Rd and the Broken River
properties.webBody:
This Advice message is being issued for Goomalibee between Frazers Road and the Broken River.
  • The large grassfire that has been burning in Goomalibee, between Frazers Rd and the Broken River is now under control.
  • Emergency services remain working in the area.
  • Some local road closures remain in place. (Road closure details below.)
  • A Community Meeting will be held at 5pm today at the Baddaginnie Fire Station, 62 Palmerston St, Baddaginnie.
  • This Advice message replaces the Advice issued at 1:09pm. 
There is currently no threat to you, but you should stay informed and monitor conditions.
High fire danger rating is forecast for Friday 19 December.
It is important to remain aware of updated information and warnings throughout the day.
What you should do: 
  • Keep the roads clear so emergency services can respond.
  • Continue to monitor conditions as situation could change rapidly.
  • Review your fire survival plan.
  • If you do not have a plan, decide what you will do if the situation changes. Find information on protecting yourself and your family: https://www.cfa.vic.gov.au/plan-prepare/am-i-at-risk/grassfires-rural.
Impacts in your area: 
  • Emergency services remain working in the area.
  • Smoke may still be visible from nearby communities and roads.
  • Local road closures still currently in place. These are at:
  • intersection of Goomalibee Rd and Tarnook Rd
  • intersection of Tarnook Rd and Webb Rd
  • intersection of Kelleher Rd and Webb Rd
  • intersection of Carroll Rd and Burness Rd
  • intersection of Terret Rd and Goomalibee
Roads are now being assessed by Benalla Rural City Council for reopening soon.
This message was issued by Country Fire Authority.

The next update is expected by 20/12/2025 09:00 am or as the situation changes.

Use multiple sources to stay informed: 
  • www.emergency.vic.gov.au
  • VicEmergency Hotline - freecall 1800 226 226
  • VicEmergency app
  • Facebook or Twitter (#vicfires)
  • Tune in to ABC Local Radio, commercial and designated community radio stations, or Sky News TV.
Accessibility:
The following services can help you, or someone you know, access information during an emergency.
  • To access this information in other languages call the Translating and Interpreting Service on 131 450 (freecall) and ask them to call VicEmergency Hotline.
  • If you are deaf, hard of hearing, or have a speech/communication impairment contact National Relay Service for assistance and ask them to call the VicEmergency Hotline.

properties.webBody:
This Advice message is being issued for Patchewollock, Yaapeet, Hopeton and Wyperfeld National Park.
  • There is a bushfire at Wyperfeld National Park - North South Track that is not yet under control.
  • The bushfire is travelling from North South Track in a north-easterly direction towards Ginap Track. 
  • This Advice replaces the Advice issued at 2.22pm.
There is currently no threat to you, but you should stay informed and plan for what you will do if the situation changes. 
What you should do: 
  • Monitor weather conditions and warnings. 
  • Review your fire survival plan. 
  • If you do not have a plan, decide what you will do if the situation changes.
Impacts in your area: 
  • Smoke may be visible from nearby communities and roads. 
  • Firefighters are responding to this fire.
This message was issued by Forest Fire Management Victoria.

The next update is expected by 19/12/2025 07:00 pm or as the situation changes.

Use multiple sources to stay informed: 
  • www.emergency.vic.gov.au
  • VicEmergency Hotline - freecall 1800 226 226
  • VicEmergency app

properties.sourceTitle: Severe Thunderstorm Warning for DAMAGING WINDS
properties.name: Severe Thunderstorm Warning for DAMAGING WINDS
properties.webHeadline:
Severe thunderstorms are likely to produce damaging winds in the warning area over the next several hours. Locations which may be affected include Mildura, Swan Hill, Echuca, Ouyen, Kerang and Walpeup.


Severe thunderstorms are no longer occurring in the North East district and the warning for this district is CANCELLED.


107 km/h wind gust was recorded at Swan Hill Airport at 2:00 pm.
